Description: Aircraft Buying, Selling, Leasing, and Financing law
Full Description: Because of the firm’s location in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma, Gilchrist Aviation Law is uniquely able to serve our clients, as well as other law firms, as special FAA counsel, special Cape Town Convention and International Registry (IR) counsel for all manner of aircraft transactions. Our firm assists clients and law firms around the world in structuring aviation transactions, whether they involve documents to be recorded with the FAA Aircraft Records Branch located in Oklahoma City, interests to be registered with the IR, located in Dublin, Ireland, or both.   The work of the firm includes legal counsel and written legal opinions regarding aircraft registration, title, financing, leasing, liens and escrow services. As special FAA Counsel, Gilchrist Aviation Law assists in the drafting and preparation of instruments, pre-positioning executed instruments in Oklahoma City in advance of closing and filing instruments with the FAA Registry upon closing. Gilchrist Aviation Law also serves as Special Cape Town Convention Counsel, advising of the “international interests” and other interests registrable on the IR and serving as IR registering agent for one or all of the parties to a transaction.   Gilchrist Aviation Law is best known in the aviation industry for the availability of our attorneys, the accuracy of our work product and counsel and the timeliness of our response to pressing client needs. Gilchrist Aviation Law has built a reputation on the level of service, quality and practicality of the counsel provided to our clients.

Brodeur and Omnicom have made Beaupre a better company by broadening our relationships, services, knowledge and capabilities around the globe. Here's the amazing part. Since being acquired, we've retained our entire management team, our brand, culture and our founding business model. We're proud of the fact that Beaupre people average nine years employment with our company; many have been with us much longer. We're equally proud of the success our clients have achieved, including more than 30 Beaupre clients acquired in major M&A deals exceeding $12 billion. We exist to get our clients where they need to go. That's our story.

Industries: Augmented Reality, Computer Vision, E-Commerce, Mobile, Shoes, Virtual Reality
Description: The vFit system consists of a smartphone App as well as a powerful database that resides remotely in the cloud.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: vFit’s mission is to help every shoe shopper find exactly what they want to buy in the size they want to buy it in, and to help every merchant, large and small, to reach those shoppers. Even with the enormous growth of Web search, proliferation of comparison-shopping sites, and expansion of online marketplaces, consumers still lack an easy way to shop for the proper size. Until now. vFit not only is the only shoe fitting technology that allows online shoe buyers the ability to compare the exact shape of their feet to the inside shape of shoes to visualize and determine the best size and fit, it is a vertical search engine for shoe shopping that puts every product, every store, every sale, coupon and discount, right at your fingertips. No matter what it is you’re looking for, you can quickly find the lowest price, the best deal, the right fit, or that hard-to-find style. vFit Shoes crawls the entire Web and with its search technology helps shoppers discover everything that online shopping has to offer. Over 2 million products from more than 60 online merchants are currently universally accessible through vFitShop.com and vFit iPhone App. vFit makes shoe shopping more efficient. Enabling shoppers to virtually try on shoes and find the product that fits, all within a single user experience. With vFit, shoppers can quickly and easily discover: What size of a certain style fits their feet or the person who they’d like to shop for. The lowest price for a product, determined from all the merchants carrying that item and size. Those hard-to-find items, or that unique and rare find.  vFit offers a variety of benefits to shoppers. For some it's finding the lowest price or the best deal; for others it's a perfect gift. Shoppers can save all their favorite styles and searches in their own virtual closet for convenience and future reference. They also can save their favorite brands to make a more specific, personalized shopping experience just for them. At vFit we're committed to continually improving our site and your shopping experience. We welcome feedback from both shoppers and merchants.
Industry Groups: Clothing and Apparel, Commerce and Shopping, Consumer Goods, Hardware, Mobile, Software
